fields.name: ref
fields.description: Reference to be used to set time

bits.name: source
bits.description:
0 = none, i.e. on receipt of message (will be inaccurate!)
1 = relative to pulse sent to EXTINT0
2 = relative to pulse sent to EXTINT1
3-15 = reserved

bits.name: fall
bits.description: use falling edge of EXTINT pulse (default rising) - only if source is EXTINT

bits.name: last
bits.description: use last EXTINT pulse (default next pulse) - only if source is EXTINT

fields.name: gnssId
fields.description:
Source of time information. Currently supported:
0 = GPS time
2 = Galileo time
3 = BeiDou time
6 = GLONASS time
7 = NavIC time

bits.name: trustedSource
bits.description:
Time is provided from a trusted source. Potentially usable for replay attack detection
0: Unknown
1: Time source can be trusted for spoofing detection

fields.name: ns
fields.description: GNSS time of week, nanosecond part from 0 to 999,999,999

fields.name: tAccNs
fields.description: Nanoseconds part of time accuracy, from 0 to 999,999,999

structure.name: UBX-MGA-INI-TIME-GNSS
structure.description: This message allows the delivery of time assistance to a receiver in a chosen GNSS timebase. This message is equivalent to the UBX-MGA-INI-TIME_UTC message, except for the time base.
